Papadi Chaat (Indian Nachos)

Chickpea Salad:
1/2 lb fingerling potatoes cut into 1/2" pieces
15 oz can (1 1/2c) cooked chickpeas, drained and rinsed
1 medium tomato, cored, seeded, and chopped
1/2 c finely chopped cucumber
1/2 c finely chopped red onion
1/4 c lemon juice
kosher salt to taste

Bring a small pot of salted water to a boil. Add the potatoes and cook until just tender when pierced with a knife, 10-12 min. Drain the potatoes and transfer to a large bowl and let cool completely. Add the chickpeas, tomato, cucumber, onion, and lemon juice. Season with salt, tossing to mix. Store in the fridge for up to 1 day and bring to room temp 20 min before serving.

Yogurt Sauce:
1/2 c whole fat greek yogurt
1/4 c lemon juice
1 tsp sugar
1/4 tsp kosher salt

In a medium bowl, mix all the ingredients until combined. Makes 3/4 c. Cover and chill in the fridge for up to 3 days. Bring to room temp 20 min before serving.

Tamarind Dressing:
1/3 c seedless tamarind paste concentrate
1/4 c water
1 1/2 tbsp honey
1/8 tsp chile powder
1/4 tsp kosher salt

In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Makes 1/2 c. Store in the fridge, covered, for up to 3 days. Bring to room temp 20 min before serving.

Assembly
3 1/2 oz papadi, fried according to the package directions (~ 4 c fried)
1/3 c pomegranate seeds
1/2 c fresh cilantro
1/4 head red cabbage, julienned (1 1/2 c)
1 large carrot peeled and julienned
1/2 small beet peeled and julienned
3" piece fresh ginger, peeled and julienned

Line a serving platter with the fried papadi. Top with the chickpea salad and drizzle with some of the yogurt sauce and the tamarind dressing. Top with the pomegranate seeds, cilantro, red cabbage, carrot, beet, and ginger. Serve with extra yogurt sauce and tamarind dressing on the side.

